  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, which typically include:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Federal money laundering charges\n- Potential felony conviction\n- Significant prison time (often 10-20 years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential forfeitures of property/funds involved\n\n3. Additional potential consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Deportation (for non-citizens)\n\nThe specific punishment depends on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Frequency of offenses\n- Specific circumstances\n- Prior criminal history\n\nDifferent jurisdictions may have slightly varying penalties, but money laundering is generally treated as a serious financial crime.",
